Sorry about the excessive amount of pasta on my feed recently, but at the same time, who could complain about pasta?! This bowl is so quick to throw together and tastes divine so I recommend you give it a go. Recipe is below so be sure to save it for later. Happy Friday my friends! Xx

Simple tomato chickpea pasta
125g pasta of choice
1/2 medium onion, chopped
1 medium carrot, peeled and chopped
2 tbsp tomato paste
1 tsp paprika
1 can chickpeas, drained and rinsed
1/2 can chopped tomatoes
2 tbsp tamari
1 tsp cumin
1 tsp coconut sugar
1 cup kale, de-stemmed and chopped
Cook the pasta according to packaging instructions. Meanwhile, add the onion, carrot, tomato paste and paprika to a non-stick frying pan and cook for 3-4 minutes, until softened and fragrant. Then, add the chickpeas together with the chopped tomatoes, tamari, cumin and coconut sugar. Stir over a medium heat for around 5 minutes, then drain and rinse the pasta and stir it in at the last minute together with the kale.

Handful spinach
Rice or noodles to serve

Simple pasta bowl I threw together for a quick lunch the other day! So flavourful and really easy to make as well, in other words 11/10 would recommend. The recipe will be down below so be sure to save this if you wanna try it out. Hope you‚Äôre all having a great Wednesday xx

Simple tomato pasta with kidney beans
125g pasta of choice
1/2 medium onion, chopped
1 medium carrot, peeled and chopped
100g mushrooms, chopped
2 tbsp tomato paste
1/2 tsp cumin
1/2 tsp garlic granules
1 can red kidney beans, drained and rinsed
1/2 can chopped tomatoes, chopped
1 tbsp tamari
Black pepper to taste
Cook the pasta according to packaging instructions. Meanwhile, add the onion and the carrot to a non-stick frying pan and cook for 3-4 minutes, until softened. Then, add the mushrooms and cook for a further 2 minutes. Add the tomato paste, cumin, and garlic granules and stir to coat the ingredients, then stir in the kidney beans together with the chopped tomatoes, tamari and black pepper. Cook over a medium heat for 4-5 minutes, then drain and rinse the pasta and stir it in until coated in the sauce.

We woke up, we hiked by headlamp the remaining stretch, we drank coffee and ate oatmeal and then we watched the sun rise from atop this lookout. It was perfect. Choc Matcha Protein Oats 
Serves 1 
Ingredients:
‚Ä¢40g rolled oats
‚Ä¢1 cup unsweetened almond milk
‚Ä¢1 scoop (30g) choc plant-based protein
‚Ä¢1 tsp matcha powder
‚Ä¢50g apple
‚Ä¢50g banana
‚Ä¢10g hemp seeds
‚Ä¢50g coconut yoghurt 
Method:
1. Add oats and milk to a pot and bring to the simmer. Cook stirring until thick and creamy.
2. Stir through protein and matcha powders.
3. Chop apple and slice banana.
4. Spoon porridge into a bowl and top with fruit, coconut yoghurt and hemp seeds.

Gluten-free pancakes made from oat flour - it‚Äôs basically oatmeal in pancake form, right?! ‚ò∫Ô∏è #saturdaybrunch #pancakes #bananapancakes #easyrecipes #glutenfreerecipes
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
INGREDIENTS
1 1/2 cup oats
2 teaspoons baking powder
1 teaspoon cinnamon
1/8 teaspoon salt
1 cup almond milk
1 egg 
1 ripe banana
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
1/2 cup chocolate chips
Coconut oil for cooking
INSTRUCTIONS
1. In a high-speed blender, place the oats, and blend until the oats become powder-like. Add the baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt to the blender and pulse once to combine. Transfer to a small bowl and set aside.
2. In the same blender, add the almond milk, egg, banana and vanilla extract, and blend until well combined.
3. Add the dry ingredients and mix until everything is well incorporated with no flour streaks. Some lumps in the batter are ok. Transfer batter to a bowl and fold in chocolate chips.
4. Scoop about 1/3 cup batter onto hot pan prepared with coconut oil and cook on medium heat for 2-3 minutes per side. Repeat for the remaining pancake batter.
5. It had been years when I was having a cultural identity crisis.
.
Even though my first language is Spanish, am I truly Mexican?
I'm a first-generation Mexican-American but am I Mexican enough?
I inherited Mexican cultural beliefs that my parents taught me, but is it enough to claim who I am?
I don't know Spanish fluently - so, do I dare to call myself Mexican?
.
I felt stuck in between my two identities: Am I too American? Or am I too Mexican?
.
A couple of years ago, I vowed myself to visit Mexico to explore my roots, my privileges, my cultural identity and who I am.
.
Here is what so interesting. The USA treats me as there is no way I can be Mexican...but Mexico treats me as I am Mexican. Two different countries, two different perspectives (for many reasons). After my two months journey in Mexico, why do I have to prove to others that I am Mexican? Why does it seem "impossible" to have two cultural identities? The world isn't so simple. There is no black and white. I didn't need them to put me into a labeled box.
.
I'm thankful for the tough, confusing journey that I've been through, and I'm thankful for all the people I've met during my journey in Mexico - because they've taught me something: I am Mexican enough.

We‚Äôre continuing the series with Peter. I‚Äôve created this pie inspired by his heritage--with a savory lumpia filling and a design modeled after Croatian folk embroidery. ‚Å£
‚Å£
‚ÄúMy father is Croatian. He left former-Yugoslavia now Bosnia Herzegovina because there wasn‚Äôt much opportunity for him. My mother is from the Philippines. They met at a dance party in Queens in 1984 and married 3 months later.
‚Å£
As a mixed-race person born and raised in NYC, with a very Eastern European name, I learned quickly that people will often see two things: what they are most comfortable with and/or what they‚Äôre most uncomfortable with. ‚Å£
Growing up in Queens, I was given the opportunity to experience many different cultures. Sering nonton serial Korea? Kemungkinan besar familiar sama Banana Milk. Coba buat sendiri yuk, nanti minumnya sambil nonton, hehe
Resep lengkap bagaimana cara membuat Banana Milk dapat dilihat di bawah: 
Bahan:
2 buah pisang cavendish matang (Sunpride), kupas, potong-potong
250 ml susu rendah lemak
1 sdm madu
1 sdt ekstrak vanilla
1 tetes pewarna makanan warna kuning (optional) 
Cara Membuat:
1. Siapkan blender. Masukkan pisang, susu rendah lemak, madu, ekstrak vanilla, dan satu tetes pewarna makanan warna kuning.
2. Blender hingga semua bahan tercampur rata dan lembut.
3. Sajikan segera atau dapat disimpan di kulkas hingga 24 jam.

VEGAN S‚ÄôMORE TRUFFLES by @itsallgoodvegan ‚ù§Ô∏è
.
S‚Äômore Truffles
2 cups graham crackers, (I used vegan cinnamon graham)
8 medjool dates, soaked in warm water
2 Tbsp maple or agave syrup
¬Ω cup almond butter, or your favorite nut butter
12 mini vegan marshmallows
1 cup chopped vegan chocolate
1 Tbsp coconut oil
.
Directions:
Place your graham crackers in a food processor or high powered blender and pulse until your graham crackers have turned into fine crumbs. Combine the graham cracker crumbs,soaked dates, almond butter, and syrup to the food processor or high powered blender. Process again until it becomes a sticky cookie dough like texture. Using a small cookie scoop place 1 tablespoon of the dough in the cookie scoop and press down. The dough should be packed lining the scooper. Place the mini marshmallow in the middle of packed cookie dough scoop. Place another tablespoon of dough on top of the marshmallow. Using your fingers press the mixture down forming a ball. Remove the dough from the cookie scoop. Using your hands form the truffle into a firm ball. Set S‚Äômore dough balls on a plate and repeat steps. Make the chocolate coating. Combine the chocolate and coconut oil in a microwave-safe bowl. Microwave for 30 second intervals stirring between each one until the chocolate has melted. Coat each dough ball with chocolate. I used a fork to do this. Place truffles on a plate and top with crushed graham crackers or marshmallows. Crispy tofu stir-fry with mushrooms and French green beans in Korean BBQ sauce by @cookingforpeanuts üß°
.
Press and dry 1-14oz block extra-firm tofu with heavy object and paper towels to remove excess liquid. Cut into bite-size cubes. Toss with some low-sodium tamari or soy sauce to lightly coat each cube. Place 3 tbsp corn starch into a freezer bag and add tofu cubes. Seal bag and shake until tofu pieces are coated with the corn starch. Make Korean BBQ sauce: In medium bowl, mix 3/4 cup low-sodium tamari or soy sauce, 3 tbsp maple syrup, 1/4 cup water, 1 tbsp rice vinegar, 1-1/2 tbsp chili paste (or to taste), 2 tsp sesame oil, 1 tsp finely minced ginger, 5 finely minced garlic cloves. In a small bowl, mix 1 tbsp cornstarch in 1 tbsp water until dissolved. Set bowls aside. Heat a little neutral oil in non-stick skillet. Add 1 lb cremini mushrooms (thickly sliced), flat side down, and let sit a few minutes before disturbing. Once bottom is dark golden-brown, saut√© and cook until both sides are the same color. Add a splash of tamari or soy sauce and cook 30 seconds. Transfer to flat plate. Add 1 lb cut French green beans to skillet and saut√© until dark golden-brown. Transfer to plate with mushrooms. Add more oil if needed and saut√© coated tofu until all sides are golden. Transfer mushrooms and green beans back into skillet with tofu. Pour sauce into a small saucepan. Bring to a gentle boil while whisking. Add the dissolved cornstarch and keep whisking. Heat while whisking until starts to thicken. Spoon desired amount of sauce into skillet with tofu and veggies. Mix well to incorporate while gently heating. Baby pumpkin pies üß° Recipe below ‚Ü¥ No bake, gluten, dairy and refined sugar free üçÇCacao buckwheat crust topped with a creamy pumpkin filling, drizzled with chocolate and topped with fresh coco whip ü•• and pecans! Make the most of the last of those pumpkins! Hope you‚Äôre having a cosy weekend xoxoxo .
.
Baby pumpkin pies (makes 8/9)
. 
Crust
.
1 cup buckwheat 
1.5 cups pecans 
2 tbsp cacao 
1.5 cups dates 
1 tbsp coconut oil 
4 tbsp water
.
Filling
.
1 can coconut milk 
1 cup pumpkin puree 
1.5 tbsp pumpkin spice 
2 tbsp maple syrup 
1 tbsp coconut oil .
Topping
.
1 can coconut milk (cream only) 
1/4 cup dark chocolate, melted 
3 tbsp chopped pecans
.
Add all crust ingredients to a blender and process until a dough is formed. Press into a lined or silicone muffin tin and set aside. Make filling by blending all filling ingredients together until smooth. Pour on top of crust and set aside in the freezer for at least four hours, or overnight. 
Whip up coconut cream with a fork and set aside in the fridge to thicken for 10 mins. Pop pies out of muffin tin/mold and drizzle with melted chocolate. Spoon coco whip into piping bag fitted with a large star tip nozzle. Swirl cream onto each cupcake and garnish with pecans. Keep in the freezer for up to a month, bring to room temperature before serving.

Gnocchi di patate e barbabietola rossa, ricetta per 6 persone

Ingredienti:
1 kg di patate (peso lordo)
150 gr di barbabietola rossa cotta (pesata cotta)
Sale, pepe
Pizzico di cannella
1 uovo medio
Farina 0 gr 300 o pi√π

Cuocete le patate, io le ho cotte a vapore in pentola pressione per 8 minuti, tagliate a fette e senza buccia. Lasciatele poi raffreddare completamente, questo permetter√† di lavorare meglio l'impasto. Una volta fredde passatele nello schiaccia patate, lavorando su una spianatoia. Aggiungete la barbabietola precedentemente frullata e tutti gli altri ingredienti e impastate. Poi aggiungete la farina man mano... Avvolgete l'impasto nella pellicola e lasciate riposare in frigo almeno 10 minuti in modo che si compatti meglio.

Ricavate tanti bastoncini e formate gli gnocchi, passandoli sulla tavoletta rigagnocchi, cos√¨ intrappoleranno pi√π condimento.
Fateli cuocere veramente poco, appena affiorano scolateli, devono essere belli sodi! Anche se l'impasto pu√≤ sembrare duro mentre lo lavorate, 300 g di farina ci vogliono tutti, altrimenti gli gnocchi verranno molto morbidi.

Credit @theendlessmeal ~
This insanely creamy Spinach Lemon Cauliflower Rice Risotto is all things delicious. It‚Äôs made with sauteed cauliflower and a healthy cauliflower cream sauce (dairy-free or regular, your choice!) and has lots of fresh lemon flavor. Top with some spicy garlic prawns for a simple to make dinner everyone will love!
~
1 tablespoon olive oil
1 medium onion, finely minced
36 ounce Cauliflower ‚ÄúRice‚Äù 
1 cup vegetable broth 
5 ounces baby spinach
OPTION #1: CHEESY LEMON CREAM SAUCE 
1 cup milk~1 cup white cheddar cheese ~1/4 cup grated parmesan cheese~1 teaspoon sea salt ~Juice of 1 lemon
OPTION #2: DAIRY-FREE LEMON CREAM SAUCE 	1 1/2 cups vegetable broth~1 cup raw cashews or pine nuts 1 tablespoon nutritional yeast~1 teaspoon sea salt~Juice of 1 lemon
THE GARLIC CHILI PRAWNS 	1 tablespoon olive oil or butter 2 garlic cloves, very finely minced  1 lb. uncooked, peeled prawns (tail on or off, your choice) 	1/2 teaspoon paprika 	A pinch of chili flakes and sea salt
Heat the oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Add the onion and cook until it is transparent, about 3-4 minutes. Add the cauliflower and broth and bring to a boil. Cook the cauliflower, stirring occasionally, until it is soft, about 8 minutes. Remove the pan from the heat. If you‚Äôre using the Cheesy Lemon Cream Sauce: Remove 2 cups of the cauliflower and add it to your blender with the milk. Blend on high until smooth. Add the cheddar, parmesan, sea salt and lemon juice and blend again until the cheese has melted. If you‚Äôre using the Dairy-Free Lemon Cream Sauce: Remove 2 cups of the cauliflower and add it to your blender with the cashews, nutritional yeast, sea salt, and lemon juice and blend on high until smooth. Add the spinach to the cauliflower rice and put the pan back on the heat. Let the spinach wilt then pour in the sauce you made and let it heat through. Either serve right away or set it aside while you make the garlic chili prawns.
